problem_text: Barutin Cove is named after the Bulgarian settlement of Barutin. Barutin Cove is on the southwest coast of Snow Island. The South Shetland Islands include Snow Island, Greenwich Island, and Deception Island. The South Shetland Islands are considered part of Antarctica. If A is located in B and B is located in C, then A is located in C.
predicates:
NamedAfter(x, y) ::: x is named after y.
Settlement(x) ::: x is a settlement.
Bulgarian(x) ::: x is Bulgarian.
Location(x, y) ::: x is located in y.
Island(x) ::: x is an island.
PartOf(x, y) ::: x is part of y.
Antarctica(x) ::: x is Antarctica.

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Barutin Cove is located in Antarctica.
tests.conclusions: ∃x ∃y ∃z (NamedAfter(barutinCove, x) ∧ Settlement(x) ∧ Bulgarian(x) ∧ Location(barutinCove, y) ∧ Island(y) ∧ PartOf(y, z) ∧ Antarctica(z)) ::: Barutin Cove is located in Antarctica. TRUE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Barutin Cove is an island in Antarctica.
tests.conclusions: Island(barutinCove) ∧ Location(barutinCove, antarctica) ::: Barutin Cove is an island in Antarctica. FALSE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If Barutin Cove is named after a Bulgarian settlement, and that settlement is located in Bulgaria, then Barutin Cove is located in Bulgaria.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Barutin Cove is named after a settlement that is located in Antarctica.
tests.conclusions: NamedAfter(barutinCove, barutin) ∧ Settlement(barutin) ∧ Bulgarian(barutin) ∧ Location(barutinCove, snowIsland) ∧ PartOf(snowIsland, southShetlandIslands) ∧ PartOf(southShetlandIslands, antarctica) ∧ Location(barutin, bulgaria) → Location(barutin, antarctica) FALSE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Barutin Cove is located in the South Shetland Islands.

Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If Barutin Cove is located on Snow Island, and Snow Island is part of the South Shetland Islands, then Barutin Cove is located in Antarctica.
tests.conclusions: Location(barutinCove, snowIsland) ∧ PartOf(snowIsland, southShetlandIslands) → Location(barutinCove, antarctica) ::: TRUE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Barutin Cove is named after a Bulgarian settlement and is located on Snow Island.
tests.conclusions: NamedAfter(barutinCove, barutin) ∧ Settlement(barutin) ∧ Bulgarian(barutin) ∧ Location(barutinCove, snowIsland) ::: TRUE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Barutin Cove is named after a Bulgarian settlement and is located in Antarctica.
tests.conclusions: NamedAfter(barutinCove, barutin) ∧ Bulgarian(barutin) ∧ Location(barutinCove, snowIsland) ∧ Island(snowIsland) ∧ PartOf(snowIsland, southShetlandIslands) ∧ PartOf(southShetlandIslands, antarctica) → (NamedAfter(barutinCove, barutin) ∧ Bulgarian(barutin) ∧ Location(barutinCove, antarctica)) FALSE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Barutin Cove is named after a Bulgarian settlement, and this settlement is located on an island that is part of Antarctica.
tests.conclusions: NamedAfter(barutinCove, barutin) ∧ Settlement(barutin) ∧ Bulgarian(barutin) ∧ Location(barutin, snowIsland) ∧ Island(snowIsland) ∧ PartOf(snowIsland, southShetlandIslands) ∧ PartOf(southShetlandIslands, antarctica) ∧ Antarctica(antarctica) ::: TRUE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Barutin Cove is located on an island that is part of Antarctica and is named after a Bulgarian settlement.
tests.conclusions: (Location(barutinCove, snowIsland) ∧ PartOf(snowIsland, antarctica)) ∧ NamedAfter(barutinCove, barutin) ∧ Bulgarian(barutin) ::: FALSE
